claim: Flublok ensures identical antigenic match with WHO- and FDA-selected flu strains.
explanation: A table listing influenza vaccine candidate viruses (A(H1N1)pdm09, A(H3N2), B/Victoria lineage, B/Yamagata lineage) and showing amino acid differences in the HA head domain at specified residue positions for cell- and egg-derived vaccine viruses and CVVs over two seasons. The table does not mention Flublok or recombinant vaccines and only details amino acid differences of cell- and egg-propagated candidate vaccine viruses; it does not support the claim that Flublok ensures an identical antigenic match with WHO- and FDA-selected strains.
